<paragraph id="B40A4A18FFEBFF9A97D1FED3FE0E9F33" blockId="8.[151,1135,322,1168]" box="[151,387,322,349]" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">
<heading id="EF42FD74FFEBFF9A97D1FED3FE0E9F33" box="[151,387,322,349]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A97D1FED3FE0E9F33" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[151,387,322,349]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mutabilis">
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A97D1FED3FE0E9F33" bold="true" box="[151,387,322,349]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">Microdon mutabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B40A4A18FFEBFF9A97D1FEF5FBB29AFE" blockId="8.[151,1135,322,1168]" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">
<bibRefCitation id="D02437E9FFEBFF9A97D1FEF5FE3D9F10" author="Schonrogge K. &amp; Barr B. &amp; Wardlaw J. C. &amp; Napper E. &amp; Gardner M. G. &amp; Breen J. &amp; Elmes G. W. &amp; Thomas J. A." box="[151,432,356,383]" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" pagination="291 - 300" refId="ref7658" refString="Schonrogge K., Barr B., Wardlaw J. C., Napper E., Gardner M. G., Breen J., Elmes G. W. &amp; Thomas J. A. 2002 a. When rare species become endangered: cryptic speciation in myrmecophilous hoverflies. Biological Journal of the Linnean Society 75: 291 - 300." type="journal article" year="2002">Schönrogge et al. (2002a</bibRefCitation>
&amp; b) ont démontré que 
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A95FCFEF5FC169F10" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[698,923,356,382]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mutabilis">
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A95FCFEF5FC169F10" box="[698,923,356,382]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">Microdon mutabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
était, jusqu’à leurs travaux, un complexe de deux espèces cryptiques, 
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A9594FE16FCEC9FCE" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[722,865,390,416]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mutabilis">
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A9594FE16FCEC9FCE" box="[722,865,390,416]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">M. mutabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et 
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A94C7FE16FB939FCE" box="[897,1054,391,416]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A94C7FE16FB979FCE" authorityName="Schonrogge, Barr, Wardlaw, Napper, Gardner, Breen, Elmes &amp; Thomas" authorityYear="2002" box="[897,1050,391,416]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="myrmicae">M. myrmicae</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
distinguables morphologiquement uniquement sur la base de critères présents chez la pupe. Les mentions suisses de 
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A96F0FE5AFDCA9F8A" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[438,583,458,484]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mutabilis">
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A96F0FE5AFDCA9F8A" box="[438,583,458,484]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">M. mutabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
antÉrieures à cette publication ne peuvent donc pas être attribuées à une espèce précise et l’identification spécifique des captures pos- tÉrieures dÉpend de la disponibilitÉ des pupes associÉes. La prÉsence en 
<collectingCountry id="CCA20A88FFEBFF9A94B9FD9FFBC59C46" box="[1023,1096,526,552]" name="Switzerland" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">Suisse</collectingCountry>
de 
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A97D1FDA0FEBD9C24" authorityName="Schonrogge, Barr, Wardlaw, Napper, Gardner, Breen, Elmes &amp; Thomas" authorityYear="2002" box="[151,304,561,586]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="myrmicae">
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A97D1FDA0FEBD9C24" box="[151,304,561,586]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">M. myrmicae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a, par la suite, été confirmée (
<bibRefCitation id="D02437E9FFEBFF9A95D1FDA1FC6C9C24" author="Speight M. C. D. &amp; Sommaggio D." box="[663,993,560,586]" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" pagination="139 - 145" refId="ref7790" refString="Speight M. C. D. &amp; Sommaggio D. 2010. On the presence in Switzerland of Microdon myrmicae Schonrogge et al., 2002, Xanthogramma dives (Rondani, 1857) and X. stackelbergi Violovitsh, 1975 (Diptera: Syrphidae). Entomo Helvetica 3: 139 - 145." type="journal article" year="2010">Speight &amp; Sommaggio 2010</bibRefCitation>
), mais, bien que de nombreuses mentions suisses existent et soient assez vraisemblablement attri- buables à 
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A9657FDE4FE299CE0" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[273,420,628,654]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mutabilis">
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A9657FDE4FE299CE0" box="[273,420,628,654]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">M. mutabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, elles demeurent non fiables car basées uniquement sur des spÉcimens adultes. Par chance, le spÉcimen adulte provenant des bords de l’Allondon, prÉsent dans les collections du MHNG, est accompagnÉ de sa pupe, celle-ci incluant un processus respiratoire antÉrieur qui est un caractère diagnostic. Il s’agit donc ainsi du premier spécimen confirmé de 
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A96B1FD6CFD089D78" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[503,645,764,790]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mutabilis">
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A96B1FD6CFD089D78" box="[503,645,764,790]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">M. mutabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
pour le canton de 
<collectingRegion id="767184FAFFEBFF9A9415FD6CFC279D79" box="[851,938,765,791]" country="Switzerland" name="Geneve" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">Genève</collectingRegion>
et pour la 
<collectingCountry id="CCA20A88FFEBFF9A9358FD6DFBE79D78" box="[1054,1130,764,790]" name="Switzerland" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">Suisse</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A9792FC8EFEEA9D56" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[212,359,798,824]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mutabilis">
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A9792FC8EFEEA9D56" box="[212,359,798,824]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">M. mutabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est une espèce de pelouses non-amendées où sa larve vit à l’inté- rieur des nids de certaines fourmis du genre 
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A95CBFCD0FD7D9D34" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[653,752,833,858]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A95CBFCD0FD7D9D34" box="[653,752,833,858]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">Formica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, en se nourrissant de leurs larves. Dans les pelouses oligotrophes de l’Étage montagnard, l’espèce est associÉe à 
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A934DFCF2FF689DF0" authorityName="Bondroit" authorityYear="1917" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lemani">
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A934DFCF2FF689DF0" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">Formica lemani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, avec laquelle elle est présente en Scandinavie et dans les îles Britanniques. Dans les pelouses plus sèches neutrophiles et calcaires, à plus basse altitude et plus au sud (par ex. 
<collectingCountry id="CCA20A88FFEBFF9A9663FC58FE029D8D" box="[293,399,969,995]" name="Belgium" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">Belgique</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="CCA20A88FFEBFF9A96DFFC58FE679D8D" box="[409,490,969,995]" name="France" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">France</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A96BAFC58FD009D8D" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[508,653,969,995]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mutabilis">
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A96BAFC58FD009D8D" box="[508,653,969,995]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">M. mutabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
peut être associée à 
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A943EFC58FBEA9D8D" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1798" box="[888,1127,969,995]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cunicularia">
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A943EFC58FBEA9D8D" box="[888,1127,969,995]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">Formica cunicularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. La fourmi 
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A9652FC7AFE519A6A" box="[276,476,1003,1028]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A9652FC7AFE559A6A" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1853" box="[276,472,1003,1028]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinerea">Formica cinerea</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
avec laquelle le spÉcimen de l’Allondon Était associÉ, est une espèce de basse altitude liée à des milieux secs, peu végétalisés et à sols sablon- neux. Les conditions actuelles du vallon de l’Allondon semblent compatibles avec les exigences de 
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A9671FBC3FE479A05" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[311,458,1105,1131]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mutabilis">
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A9671FBC3FE479A05" box="[311,458,1105,1131]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">M. mutabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et de sa fourmi hôte. Des recherches dans ce secteur seraient intéressantes afin d’établir si cette espèce de 
<taxonomicName id="73B5319BFFEBFF9A95A2FBE2FCD89AE3" box="[740,853,1139,1165]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="86C1960AFFEBFF9A95A2FBE2FCD89AE3" box="[740,853,1139,1165]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="95">Microdon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est encore prÉsente.
</paragraph>
